Portable, the street rave of the moment has revealed YBNL boss, Olamide aka Baddo Sneh has become his all-time benefactor. The self-styled ‘wahala musician’ who recently fell out with his promoter Kogbagidi due to allegedly being choked with ‘over packaging’, also noted Baddo has taken up everything that concerns him. Speaking during the interview, the “Zazoo Zeh” crooner disclosed the video for his hit track which brought him to limelight was paid for by Olamide while he also mentioned other ways he has continued to be a blessing to him. Portable said: “Olamide is my baddo! He blessed me, he didn’t borrow me. He said: “I give it to you for free.” He is the one in charge of everything that concerns me. He tells me; “Do this, do that.”   Eight Nigerian celebrities with dual citizenship     Davido is Africa’s most followed artiste on Twitter     Eight famous musicians earning billions years after death   - Advertisement - “The recent song I just dropped “Ogo Forever”, it was baddo that called me and told me “I want you to drop this kind of song. I saw one freestyle. Go right ahead and drop the song.” And I did it. He has also promised to foot the bill for the video. “The Zazoo Zeh video, Olamide paid for it. He didn’t collect a dime. He is the sponsor, everything. Olamide paid the producer, paid for studio and everything else. “To the person that now promotes my songs, same Olamide introduced me to him. He said; ‘Zeh, let them handle it for you, so all the proceeds can be entering your account.” Because I fought for my right. If I didn’t fight for my right, I wouldn’t understand the business. “So, baddo took me there and settled everything. He said to me, “Portable, no vex. It’ll be like this and that so Zeh” and I zeh, that’s all.”